-- Ziraat Bankasi May Partner With Syria's Commercial Bank, Hurriyet Reports
-- Ercan Ersoy
-- 2010-06-18T05:46:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/ziraat-bankasi-may-partner-with-syria-s-commercial-bank-hurriyet-reports.html

          
          
             TC Ziraat Bankasi AS, largest
Turkish bank by assets, may set a partnership with Commercial
Bank of Syria,  Hurriyet  reported, citing  Adnan Ahmad Yusuf , head
of Arab Banks Association.  
 More Turkish banks may form joint ventures in Middle
Eastern countries and as many as four banks from Saudi Arabia,
Qatar and Bahrain are interested in entering the Turkish market,
Yusuf said, according to the newspaper.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Ercan Ersoy  in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  
          
          


  


        